          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "president of the carriage of the Ark.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Was for song.—So the LXX., which reads “leader of the songs;” but the Syriac has “bore the burden daily” and although the word massâ—i.e., “lifting up,” or “bearing”—might mean “lifting up the voice,” (1) the context is against that meaning here, for Heman, Asaph, and Ethan were conductors of the singing and music; (2) Chenaniah is nowhere else associated with music (see Note on 1Chronicles 26:29); (3) the word massâ, “bearing,” has the sense we have given it when used in relation to Levites (Numbers 4:19; 2Chronicles 35:3).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Was for song.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—So the LXX., which reads “leader of the songs;” but the Syriac has “bore the burden daily” and although the word ",
            "children": []
