  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And Chenaniah chief of the Levites was for song,.... But the chief for the song were Heman, Asaph, and Ethan; rather ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for the burden, as the Targum; for the lifting up and bearing the ark: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "he instructed about the song; or about the taking up and bearing the burden, the ark; directing when to take it up, and how far to go with it, and then rest: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "because he was skilful; a wise and prudent man in all things, and so proper to direct in this business. ",
        "children": [
